  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the predictive factors of poor compliance to sleep
      disordered breathing therapy in chronic heart failure patients treated for central sleep
      apnea. To characterize nocturia pathophysiology associated with SDB in this population. To
      use telemonitoring data to define predictive factors of poor compliance.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
